The Nigerian Association of Chambers of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (NACCIMA) has commiserated with The Guardian on the passage of its Photo Editor, Mr Femi Adebesin-Kuti. In a condolence letter to The Guardian, the Director-General of NACCIMA, Mr Olusola Obadimu described the late Adebesin-Kuti as a passionate and dedicated photojournalist. “During his lifetime, Mr Femi Adebesin-Kuti was a passionate and dedicated photojournalist. His death is indeed a huge loss to the Guardian Newspaper and the Nigeria Union of Journalist. We at the Chamber of Commerce Movement in Nigeria deeply mourn and commiserate with the Guardian Newspaper, family and loved ones,” the letter reads in part. 